text: Sunflower County is a county found in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 25,971 people lived there. Indianola is the largest city and county seat. It is in the Mississippi Delta region. Sunflower County was created in 1844. == References == Category:1840s establishments in Mississippi Category:1844 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
title: Sunflower County, Mississippi
